CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1778193329
OL,3,CPrinting delay leaves some unable to
OL,4,Cvote in Senedd Election
OL,6,FAfter receiving criticism around
OL,7,Fundelivered postal votes, a Royal Mail
OL,8,Fspokesperson said all their deliveries
OL,9,Fhad been completed as expected.
OL,11,F"In response to complaints from
OL,12,Fconstituents relating to undelivered
OL,13,Fpostal packs, Royal Mail has been
OL,14,Fadvised by the Council that the ballot
OL,15,Fpapers in question were not printed
OL,16,Fand, as such, were never handed over
OL,17,Fto Royal Mail for delivery.
OL,26,@sD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,469,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1778193329
OL,3,CPrinting delay leaves some unable to
OL,4,Cvote in Senedd Election
OL,6,F"All ballot packs received by Royal
OL,7,FMail in the area have been processed
OL,8,Fand delivered as expected. Any further
OL,9,Fenquiries relating to the missing
OL,10,Fpacks should therefore be directed to
OL,11,Fthe Council."
OL,13,FThe Electoral Commission advised that
OL,14,Fif a voter is yet to receive their
OL,15,Fpostal ballot, and is at home, they
OL,16,Fcan request a replacement in person
OL,17,Ffrom their local authority.
OL,26,@sD@MO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/11
